Recommendations
To address the identified gaps, GreenLeaf Organics should:
Implement least privilege access to restrict employee access to sensitive data.
Develop and enforce a disaster recovery plan and regular backup process.
Strengthen password policies and implement multi-factor authentication (MFA).
Encrypt all sensitive data, both at rest and in transit.
Deploy an Intrusion Detection System (IDS) to monitor for potential threats.
Conduct regular employee training on cybersecurity best practices.
Update privacy policies and ensure compliance with GDPR and PCI DSS.
By addressing these gaps, GreenLeaf Organics can significantly improve its security posture and reduce the risk of fines, breaches, and reputational damage.


